rComments: omg so boring and a tad sus. i felt like he hated us as students because why else would anyone do this job if you were so bad at it? He talks about Indigenous peoples like he's some sort of expert but my roommate was also in the class would always tell me "um, he's wrong and that's kind of racist"
Prof Rück is one of the nicest profs I've had. I took EAS 1101 with him too and he's always been super lovely, kind, and caring. Very knowledgeable and sweet.

Saw the good ratings for this prof on here, figured he'd be a decent prof but turned out to be pretty overrated. Didn't strike me as super enthusiastic about the class and his grading criteria was unclear. Pretty dismissive (notably with the group presentations) and didn't really give much direction for the exam.

Pretty good prof, the content is interesting and he teaches it well. There's a lot of reading assignments, but they're very easy to ace assuming you actually did the readings. Only complaint was a group project worth 30% of the course grade - felt a bit unfair that so much of your grade hinges on getting a good group, which I didn't..
Great prof, fun class, super respectful and accessible. I'd take another course with him again any day. Lots of group discussions and class participation, interesting readings and content.

Great prof! Super aware of his own privilege/limitations as a non-Indigenous person teaching an Indigenous studies course and is really good at facilitating discussion. Had guest speakers and a field trip which broadened the class experience. Easy A if you do the readings and reflect on them and connect it to the class material.
Really nice guy, very dedicated to his subject. Interesting classes and fun assignments. loved the class wish I could take it again.

We had to do weekly reading responses, but as long as you read the text and responded well you got 100%. He really cares about the subject and scheduled lots of speakers and class trips to enhance our learning. Excellent class, and would definitely take one of his classes again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: 20% of your grade is from weekly reading responses and by just simply doing them is an easy 100%. The midterm and final require you to really pay attention in class and connect with the readings from each week. Also don't take a class immediately after this one, because he always goes over and gets mad if you leave while he's still lecturing

20% of our grade was based on reading responses based on chapters from the readings or videos/ podcasts of the week and you got 100% on them if you proved that you did the readings. Prof Ruck is a really nice guy and teaches the course really well! The course itself is a MUST in my opinion great material and lots of guest speakers.

Rück was a very funny and easy going professor. Only assignments were weekly reading responses (that you have to read for every week- but dont worry they are short readings). His midterm however had questions I had no idea the answer to (they must have been mentioned once by him- they werent on his slides). You must attend class and listen close

Ruck is very clear in his course expectations and respects his students. He is very responsive to emails and is understanding. His course for Seminar is reading-heavy, but course discussions, reading responses and the interesting nature of the readings help get you through it. Expectations are high, but he is there to help!

Sure he is a tough grader but his expectations are clear and the lectures are really lively and interesting. Guest speakers, field trip, videos. I'm in university to learn, and this is the kind of class I'm here for.

Great prof and the class is really interesting. He uses videos and guest speakers which makes it more interesting. Overall great class and prof. Reading responses are due every week but they are super easy and it is basically a 20% given also, readings are interesting. Recommend attending any field trip, it is most likely exam material.

He had slides which were completely useless because he posted nothing on them. Exams were a complete surprise because he wouldn't even hint what would be on them out of the large amount of material we covered. Amazing class and content, wish it were taught by someone else.

You'll learn so much from this class. He clearly knows his stuff and you can see how passionate he is about the topics discussed. The reading assignments are pretty easy to do. The midterm and final were both lecture and reading heavy.

His lectures are interesting but you never know what is the important information to take down. Exams and tests are a surprise since he never gives information on what will be on them. He is very vague when asking about final exam/midterm. Would not take his classes again. But he was a nice professor. TA also is a very hard marker.

One of the best classes I've taken. He uses a lot of clips, films, and guest speakers to enhance his lectures and the readings are really interesting. There are a decent amount of readings for this class and they're essential to do well on tests. Evaluations are reading responses almost every week, a midterm, and a final (MC, T/F, SA).
Fascinating class with awesome field trip. Very kind, helpful professor.
Wonderful professor. Challenging work. Hard grader. Stimulating lectures. Probably learned more in this class than any other. Very helpful outside of class. Recommended.
One of the most interesting classes I've taken so far--This prof knows a huge amount on this topic and brings in great guest speakers, videos, and field trips.

Prof makes subject matter relevant to today's world. Interesting lectures, but reading heavy course. Notes aren't posted online so attending class is crucial to getting a good grade. Loved this class, would take it again!
Loved this class! Prof has high expectations but he made these clear in the first class. He seems to enjoy talking to students during office hours and I found him really helpful when I had questions.
I took this class as an elective, it was very interesting and I learned a lot, but the prof is socially awkward and if you need help for a paper, don't expect him to help.

Tough grader but one of the best classes I could've ever taken. His classes are very interesting. Instead of a lecture, one day we had the chance to do a walking tour and learnt about Ottawa through the eyes of an Indigenous person. Lots of guest speakers. The class gave me a better understanding of our history and I'm walking out a better person.

He's really nice but the class was SO dense. So much reading and the lectures are so packed with information. He doesn't slow down and he doesn't post the notes online and he assigns a ton of reading. He has really high standards so don't think that because it's an elective it'll be an easy pass
One of my favourite classes this semester
